<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="979" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d979">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.11/7645</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">
                                <gloss type="from">Pacific Mail Steamship Company</gloss> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San Francisco</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 30, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your wire 29th. Our steamer <hi rend="italic">Newport</hi> ordered call
                            Manzanillo northbound; due there about third or fourth. Passenger
                            certificate only allows 68 cabin, 42 steerage. Number passengers on
                            board not known. If United States Government instructs collector of this
                            port that no penalty or fine will be inflicted on Pacific Mail Steamship
                            Company or steamer <hi rend="italic">Newport</hi> if she brings on this
                            voyage people in excess of her certificates we will instruct Captain <hi rend="italic">Newport</hi> to take all passengers he can accommodate
                            at Mexican ports otherwise many may be refused passage.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pacific Mail Steamship Company</hi>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>